<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-04T17:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-04T17:36:00-05:00" n="312" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.61383 J 41/75: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-04T16:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">December 4,
                                        1920—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:03
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>468. The following telegram has been received from Consular Agent Jenkins
                            at Puebla dated today: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Federal Judge rendered decision in my case this morning
                                    declaring that all proof against me had disappeared and placing
                                    me in liberty canceling my bond. I have certified copy of his
                                    decision which I will deliver to you Monday.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>